# Using prepare() and execute()

With PDO, you use `prepare()` to send the query with placeholders, then `execute()` to send the actual values.

```php
$stmt = $pdo->prepare('SELECT * FROM users WHERE email = :email');
$stmt->execute(['email' => $email]);
$user = $stmt->fetch();
```

Placeholders can be named (`:email`) or positional (`?`).

```php
<?php
// Positional placeholders (?)
$stmt = $pdo->prepare('SELECT * FROM users WHERE age > ? AND city = ?');
$stmt->execute([18, 'Paris']);

// Named placeholders
$stmt = $pdo->prepare('SELECT * FROM users WHERE age > :age AND city = :city');
$stmt->execute(['age' => 18, 'city' => 'Paris']);

// You can also bind parameters individually
$stmt->bindParam(':age', $age, PDO::PARAM_INT);
$stmt->bindParam(':city', $city, PDO::PARAM_STR);
$stmt->execute();
?>
```
